CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 6, 1957, page 2, reads: "Close-up of Rubble - This is the spot (shown by arrow) where one child tumbled down the steep, cliff-like slope to the new rataining wall. Rubble left on lot, which makes it an eyesore for the neighborhood, in shown in the photograph. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Lot of demolished house with debris, sidewalk, and car on the right along Miller Street in the Hill District
